article_title: Medicaid, CHIP add 10.1 million since insurance marketplaces opened
article_text: More than 10.1 million people have enrolled in Medicaid and the Children’s Health Insurance Program in the first 14 months since marketplace enrollment began, the Obama administration reported Monday.
